The paper deals with face recognition using regression analysis, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using a matrix-based error model, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG) and involves optimization using the alternating direction method of multipliers (ADMM), which is a popular optimization technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with occlusion and illumination changes, which are common challenges in multimedia processing (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT).
